
required libraries ( DEBIAN / RPM ) :
 - libextlib-ocaml-dev / ocaml-extlib-devel
 - libpcre-ocaml-dev / ??

additional libraries (enable compilation with --with-<library>) :
 - libpostgresql-ocaml-dev / ocaml-postgresql-devel
 - libsqlite3-ocaml-dev / ocaml-sqlite-devel
 - libzip-ocaml-dev / ?
 - libbz2-ocaml-dev and libbz2-dev / ?
 - libjson-static-camlp4-dev / ?
 - libocamlgraph-ocaml-dev / ?
 - libounit-ocaml-dev / ocaml-ounit-devel
 - librpm-dev / librpm-devel

To use rpm support, dose3 needs librpm > 4.6

To compile from git :
aclocal -I m4
autoconf
./configure
make

--with-rpm
--with-xml
--with-ocamlgraph
--with-sqlite
--with-postgresql
--with-zip
--with-bz2
--with-oUnit

libcudf is included in the source tree of dose3 (but not in the dose3 release tarball). 
To use the version of libcudf in the source tree you can specify
--without-libcudf as configure option. By default dose3 uses the system wide version
of libcudf.

Ex :
./configure --without-libcudf --with-xml --with-ocamlgraph --with-zip --with-oUnit --with-bz2 --with-rpm

In order to compile the a selection of applications do "make". To compile specific application

$cd applications/
$ocamlbuild $app.native
